        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         If you cast a DoT, FD, then get back up while the DoT is on, the mob will aggro you.</P><P>FD only fails on success if you are in melee range. In all cases where we've been pounded on after FD, it's because we are in melee range. I've seen the same thing with my monk while bashing shady at the bazaar. Me and another monk were wacking on shady then he says i'd better feign cause he can't kill him. So i promptly feign and he backs off and does the same but suddenly continues to smack me. I'm guessing it's one of those things where the mob is in mid-swing when FD lands and he finishes his attack while you've just FD and then notices you're not dead and beats on you some more. Kinda like with the new pet changes, if you ST a mob right when your pet is wacking it, he will break mez and you won't get a "I can not awake..."</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
