         Hm far as I know (which ain't much)...</P><P>If you have cast on a mob that's highish level it will spread aggro to others, if it's lower level it wont, so that's where the Skyfire thing versus katta maybe occuring? Blues versus light blues/greens??<BR>You know like the "high level can pull singles" thing.</P><P>generally getting BELOW water/lava breaks aggro if your a distance away, a *different* environment? Similar for boats?</P><P>Some mobs have PSYCHO aggro like some bits of luclin and Hate. I can cast mala/Malosini on an inc mob in Hate and get smashed, despite tanks thumping the mob on way to me, normally Malo line is *extremely* low aggro and an arrow can aggro off, never mind melee and taunt.</P><P>From what monsk say roaming and static mobs have different aggro, roamers its hard for FD to work right, static mobs after going back to spawn point sort of "reset" aggro and it's clear.<BR>Again, Skyfire versus Katta.</P><P>Ask on Monkly Business boards? they're bound to know :)</P><P>Redorious<BR>Archmage<BR>karana</P><P><BR><a href="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.silverblades-suitcase.com/artofadreamer/3d/excalibur2thumb.jpg" border=0></a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
